cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.IR, cs.DS 

This paper discusses the friendship paradox in the context of Twitter, which falls under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the impact of increased activity on information overload, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). The analysis of cascades and virality falls under the category of data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the correlation between Twitter activity and number of friends/followers, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SI).
